title-'THE AUSTRIAN ENVIRONMENTAL SIGN',
titleGerman-'DAS &Atilde;STERREICHISCHE UMWELTZEICHEN',
titleEnglish-'THE AUSTRIAN ENVIRONMENTAL SIGN',
descriptionCategoryKeyword-'Symbol',
year-1991,
design-'Vienna, March - May 1989 I: Umweltgerecht - Environmentally considerate 29.6 x 20.7 cm, watercolour and pencil on paper, not signed / not dated II: 29.6 x 20.9 cm, watercolour on paper, not signed / not dated III: 29.6 x 20.9 cm, watercolour on paper, not signed / not dated IV: Umweltfreundlich - Environmentally friendly 29.6 x 20.9 cm, watercolour and pencil on paper, not signed / not dated V: Umweltfreundlich 29.6 x 20.9 cm, watercolour on paper, not signed / not dated VI +  VIa: Umweltfreundlich 29.6 x 20.9 cm, watercolour on paper, not signed / not dated VII: Umweltfreundlicher 29.6 x 20.9 cm, watercolour on paper, not signed / not dated VIII: Umweltzeichen - Environmental sign 29.6 x 20.9 cm, watercolour and ink on paper, not signed / not dated IX: &Atilde; 18.5 cm, watercolour on a copy of VIII, not signed / not dated X: &Atilde; 18.5 cm, watercolour on a copy of VIII, not signed / not dated XI: &Atilde; 20 cm, watercolour on a copy of VIII, not signed / not dated XII: 29.6 x 20.9 cm, watercolour on a copy of VIII, not signed / not dated XIII: Umweltzeichen 29.6 x 19.3 cm, instructions of the artist on a proff, not signed / not dated XIV: 29.6 x 21 cm, watercolour on a black and white copy of VIII, not signed / not dated XV: 29.6 x 21 cm, watercolour on a black and white copy of VIII, not signed / not dated XVI: 29.6 x 21 cm, watercolour on a black and white copy of VII, not signed / not dated XVII: 29.6 x 21 cm, watercolour on a black and white copy of X, not signed / not dated XVIII: 29.6 x 21 cm, watercolour on a black and white copy of X, not signed / not dated XIX: &Atilde; 19 cm, watercolour on a black and white copy of X, not signed / not dated XX: &Atilde; 19.5 cm, watercolour on a black and white copy of XI, not signed / not dated XXI: 29.6 x 20.2 cm, watercolour and collage, not signed / not dated  3 designs fo September 13, 1990 Each 30.2 x 21 cm, watercolour on a photograph: red, green, blue Not signed All: Private collection, Vienna',
information_ge-'Im Auftrag des &Atilde;sterreichischen Bundesministeriums f&Atilde;&frac14;r Umwelt, Jugend und Familie, Minister Marilies Flemming. Das Umweltzeichen kann jedes Produkt erhalten, das auf Grund einer Umstellung des Verfahrens oder einer prinzipiell umweltfreundlichen Herstellungsart weniger umweltbelastend ist als andere und somit einen Beitrag zum Schutz unseres Lebensraumes leistet. Hundertwassers Entwurf stellt einen Erdball dar, der von einem Ring umgeben ist. Rund um diesen Erdball wachsen gr&Atilde;&frac14;n-blaue B&Atilde;&curren;ume als Symbol f&Atilde;&frac14;r Vegetation und Luft. Das Umweltzeichen war in verschiedenen Farbvarianten geplant: Gr&Atilde;&frac14;n: f&Atilde;&frac14;r Produkte, die in mehreren Kategorien umweltfreundlicher sind Blau: f&Atilde;&frac14;r besonderen Schutz von Luft und Wasser Braun: f&Atilde;&frac14;r Schutzma&Atilde;nahmen f&Atilde;&frac14;r den Boden, f&Atilde;&frac14;r die Pflanzen- oder Tierwelt Rot: f&Atilde;&frac14;r Umweltma&Atilde;nahmen, die zur Einsparung von Energie f&Atilde;&frac14;hren Gelb: f&Atilde;&frac14;r L&Atilde;&curren;rmschutzvorkehrungen. 1991 wurde das Umweltzeichen erstmals vergeben.',
information_en-'Commissioned by the Austrian Federal Ministry for the Environment, Youth and the Family under Minister Marilies Flemming. The environmental sign can be awarded to any product which is less of a burden on the environment than others thanks to improvements in production resulting in fundamentally environment-friendly processes, and which thus contributes to protecting our habitat. Hundertwasser&#039;s design features a globe surrounded by a ring. Around this globe, green and blue trees are growing, symbols of vegetation and air. The environmental sign was intended  in various colours: green: for products which are more environmentally friendly in several categories blue: for particular protection of air and water brown: for steps taken to protect the soil and the plant or animal world red: for environmental steps which lead to a reduction of required energy yellow: for steps to reduce noise levels. The evironmental sign was awarded for the first time in 1991.',
literatureMonographs-['objekt'-'Objekt 1257', 'storage'-'Bibliothek'],
literatureExhibitionCatalogues-['exhibition'-'KunstHausWien,Vienna', 'year'-2008, 'pointer'-'pp. 217 (c)', 'city'-294],
reproductionsArtPrints-'Poster: World Tech Vienna, 1991 (Oct. 23-27)'
]).

