information_en-'Hundertwasser created three colour variants after work 944 for the poster Imagine Tomorrow&#039;s World (see APA 332). The fourth variant shows the colours of the original. In conjunction with the postage stamp, a commemorative sheet was published in an edition of 80,000, consisting of the Hundertwasser commemorative block of postage stamps, bearing the special cancellation stamp, as well as a black and white print of the set. The cover page of the commemorative sheet is decorated with a detail of the engraving after work 944. Published on the occasion of WIPA 2000 (International postage stamp exhibition ) in Vienna.',
