title-'ANSCHLUSS II - EU VERRAT AN &Atilde;STERREICH',
titleGerman-'ANSCHLUSS II - EU VERRAT AN &Atilde;STERREICH',
titleEnglish-'E.U. - Betrayal of Austria',
descriptionCategoryKeyword-'Sticker',
year-1994,
design-'I Vienna, January 13, 1994 29.5 x 21 cm Watercolour and pencil on paper Not signed Private collection, Vienna  II Vienna, January 13, 1994 29.5 x 21 cm Watercolour and pencil on paper Not signed Private collection, Vienna  III Vienna, January 13, 1994 29.5 x 21 cm Watercolour and pencil on paper Not signed Private collection, Vienna (realised)',
information_ge-'Entwurf f&Atilde;&frac14;r Poster und Sticker anl&Atilde;&curren;&Atilde;lich Hundertwassers Einsatz gegen den Beitritt &Atilde;sterreichs zu EU. Entwurf III wurde realisiert. Schon in einem Text von 1988 hielt Hundertwasser fest, da&Atilde; ein Anschlu&Atilde; an die EU keine gute Sache f&Atilde;&frac14;r &Atilde;sterreich w&Atilde;&curren;re und da&Atilde; &Atilde;sterreich im Falle eines Beitritts zur EU seine Eigenst&Atilde;&curren;ndigkeit, seine Unabh&Atilde;&curren;ngigkeit, seine Neutralit&Atilde;&curren;t und seine Glaubw&Atilde;&frac14;rdigkeit als friedliebende Kulturnation im Herzen Europas verlieren w&Atilde;&frac14;rde. In den Jahren 1993 und 1994 trat Hundertwasser immer wieder vehement gegen einen Beitritt &Atilde;sterreichs zur Europ&Atilde;&curren;ischen Union ein und formulierte seine Bedenken in dem Manifest EU Beitritt ist Verrat an &Atilde;sterreich und Verrat an Europa. (siehe S. 1150).',
information_en-'Design for poster and sticker on the occasion of Hundertwasser&#039;s activities against Austria&#039;s joining of the E. U. Design III was realised. As early as 1988, Hundertwasser noted in an essay that integration in the E. U. was not a good solution for Austria, and that Austria would lose its independence, its autonomy, its neutrality and its credibility as a peace-loving culture nation at the heart of Europe if the country were to join the E. U. During 1993 and 1994 Hundertwasser repeatedly and emphatically spoke out against Austria&#039;s joining of the European Union. He expressed his reservations in the manifesto To Join the E. U. Is to Betray Austria and Betray Europe. (see p. 1150)',
literatureMonographs-['objekt'-'Objekt 1257', 'storage'-'Bibliothek']
]).

